CreateExclusionGroupRequest.name: CreateExclusionGroupRequest
CreateExclusionGroupRequest.description: Given a title entity token and exclusion group details, will create a new exclusion group for the title.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description of the exclusion group.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Friendly name of the exclusion group.

properties.name: ExclusionGroupId
properties.description: Identifier of the exclusion group.

CreateExperimentRequest.name: CreateExperimentRequest
CreateExperimentRequest.description: Given a title entity token and experiment details, will create a new experiment for the title.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description of the experiment.

properties.name: Duration
properties.description: The duration of the experiment, in days.

properties.name: EndDate
properties.description: When experiment should end.

properties.name: ExclusionGroupId
properties.description: Id of the exclusion group.

properties.name: ExclusionGroupTrafficAllocation
properties.description: Percentage of exclusion group traffic that will see this experiment.

properties.name: ExperimentType
properties.description: Type of experiment.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Friendly name of the experiment.

properties.name: SegmentId
properties.description: Id of the segment to which this experiment applies. Defaults to the 'All Players' segment.

properties.name: StartDate
properties.description: When experiment should start.

properties.name: TitlePlayerAccountTestIds
properties.description: List of title player account IDs that automatically receive treatments in the experiment, but are not included when calculating experiment metrics.

properties.name: Variants
properties.description: List of variants for the experiment.

properties.name: ExperimentId
properties.description: The ID of the new experiment.

GetTreatmentAssignmentRequest.name: GetTreatmentAssignmentRequest
GetTreatmentAssignmentRequest.description: Given a title player or a title entity token, returns the treatment variants and variables assigned to the entity across all running experiments

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The optional entity to perform this action on. Defaults to the currently logged in entity.

properties.name: TreatmentAssignment
properties.description: Treatment assignment for the entity.

properties.name: ConfidenceIntervalEnd
properties.description: The upper bound of the confidence interval for the relative delta (Delta.RelativeValue).

properties.name: ConfidenceIntervalStart
properties.description: The lower bound of the confidence interval for the relative delta (Delta.RelativeValue).

properties.name: DeltaAbsoluteChange
properties.description: The absolute delta between TreatmentStats.Average and ControlStats.Average.

properties.name: DeltaRelativeChange
properties.description: The relative delta ratio between TreatmentStats.Average and ControlStats.Average.

properties.name: InternalName
properties.description: The machine name of the metric.

properties.name: Movement
properties.description: Indicates if a movement was detected on that metric.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: The readable name of the metric.

properties.name: PMove
properties.description: The expectation that a movement is real

properties.name: PValue
properties.description: The p-value resulting from the statistical test run for this metric

properties.name: PValueThreshold
properties.description: The threshold for observing sample ratio mismatch.

properties.name: StatSigLevel
properties.description: Indicates if the movement is statistically significant.

properties.name: StdDev
properties.description: Observed standard deviation value of the metric.

properties.name: Value
properties.description: Observed average value of the metric.

properties.name: DateGenerated
properties.description: Represents the date the scorecard was generated.

properties.name: Duration
properties.description: Represents the duration of scorecard analysis.

properties.name: EventsProcessed
properties.description: Represents the number of events processed for the generation of this scorecard

properties.name: ExperimentId
properties.description: Id of the experiment.

properties.name: ExperimentName
properties.description: Friendly name of the experiment.

properties.name: LatestJobStatus
properties.description: Represents the latest compute job status.

properties.name: SampleRatioMismatch
properties.description: Represents the presence of a sample ratio mismatch in the scorecard data.

properties.name: ScorecardDataRows
properties.description: Scorecard containing list of analysis.

properties.name: IsControl
properties.description: Represents whether the variant is control or not.

properties.name: MetricDataRows
properties.description: Data of the analysis with the internal name of the metric as the key and an object of metric data as value.

properties.name: PlayerCount
properties.description: Represents the player count in the variant.

properties.name: VariantName
properties.description: Name of the variant of analysis.
